# Pydantic Schemas

## Always separate request and response schemas

```python
# ❌ BAD — one model for both input and output
class Match(BaseModel):
    id: int
    title: str

# ✅ GOOD
class MatchRequest(BaseModel):
    title: str
    location: str

class MatchResponse(BaseModel):
    id: int
    title: str
    location: str

    model_config = {"from_attributes": True}
```

Naming: `{Entity}Request` for input, `{Entity}Response` for output.

## Use `model_validate()` to convert ORM → response

```python
# ✅ GOOD
@router.get("/{match_id}")
async def get_match(...) -> MatchResponse:
    match = await match_repo.get_by_id(match_id)
    return MatchResponse.model_validate(match)
```

## Never expose sensitive fields in responses

Response schemas explicitly whitelist fields. Internal fields (hashed password, raw tokens, internal IDs) must not appear in any `*Response` schema.

## Do not use `RootModel`

```python
# ❌ BAD
class IdList(RootModel[list[int]]): ...

# ✅ GOOD
async def bulk(ids: Annotated[list[int], Body(min_length=1)]): ...
```
